Samsung recently launched its new Galaxy Note 10 and Note 10+ smartphones in South Africa, offering powerful performance and flagship devices. Both devices boast high-end hardware, including AMOLED displays, quad-lens camera systems, and the Note range’s signature S-Pen. Samsung has centred the front-facing camera on the Note 10 and slimmed down the device’s chassis compared to the previous generation. The S-Pen has also been improved again, and now supports wireless gesture control which lets you remotely control the smartphone’s interface from a distance. Both Galaxy Note 10 models include an in-screen fingerprint sensor and IP68 water and dust resistance. Cash prices currently listed for the devices on Takealot are: We compared some of the best offers from Vodacom, MTN, Cell C, and Telkom for these new premium smartphones in South Africa. The available contract prices for the Samsung Galaxy Note 10 and Note 10+ across all mobile operators are shown below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-317153" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Samsung-Note-10-.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Samsung-Note-10-.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Samsung-Note-10--300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Samsung-Note-10--595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-315843" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Samsung-Galaxy-Note-10-1.jpg" alt="Samsung Galaxy Note 10 1" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Samsung-Galaxy-Note-10-1.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Samsung-Galaxy-Note-10-1-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Sa